### Osquery — Query Profiles `Experimental`

> Query profiling is enabled by default. To disable it globally, add the following to the Advanced Osquery configuration in your Fleet integration policy:
>
> ```json
> {
>   "elastic_options": {
>     "profiling": {
>       "profiling_all": false
>     }
>   }
> }
> ```

#### How to use this dashboard

**Query profiles** show how expensive each osquery query is per host. Each document is one execution, correlatable via `response_id`.

Source types distinguish how a query was triggered:

* **Live** — ad-hoc queries run on demand from the Osquery live queries interface
* **Recurring rule** — RRULE-scheduled runs, managed via Kibana pack scheduling
* **Scheduled** — native `osquery_schedule` metrics, configured in your pack
